updated_cases.title: Measure SSL Handshake Time (By Sniffer)
updated_cases.custom_steps:
1. Start a Sniffer at NSproxy
2. Send a imitaion SSL Client Hello packet from Client to www.box.com
3. Copy the timestamp of SSL Client Hello while recieving from Client (SSL_Client_Hello)
4. Copy the timestamp of SSL Finished while forwarding from NSproxy (SSL_FIN)
5. X-NS-SSL-HANDSHAKE-TIME should be SSL_FIN - SSL_Client_Hello

updated_cases.title: Measure SSL Handshake Time (By Log)
updated_cases.custom_steps:
1. Start a watson log level synthetic to 5 at NSproxy
2. Send a imitaion SSL Client Hello packet from Client to www.box.com
3. Copy the timestamp of SSL Client Hello while seeing the log "start ssl handshake time: " (SSL_Client_Hello)
4. Copy the timestamp of SSL Finished while seeing the log "stop ssl handshake time: " (SSL_FIN)
5. X-NS-SSL-HANDSHAKE-TIME should be SSL_FIN - SSL_Client_Hello

updated_cases.title: Using GRE as ACM to Measure Transmit Time
updated_cases.custom_summary: Using GRE as ACM to Measure Transmit Time
updated_cases.custom_steps:
1. Start a watson log level synthetic to 5 at NSproxy
2. Setup GRE tunneling from GRE agent to Proxy
3. Send a imitaion SSL Client Hello packet from Client to www.box.com
4. Copy the timestamp of HTTP Request while seeing the log "start req transit time: " (HTTP_REQ_HDR_RESUME)
5. Copy the timestamp of HTTP Request while seeing the log "stop req transit time: " (HTTP_REQ_HDR_SENT)
6. Request_Transit_Time should be HTTP_REQ_HDR_SENT - HTTP_REQ_HDR_RESUME
7. Copy the timestamp of HTTP Request while seeing the log "start resp transit time: " (HTTP_RES_HDR)
8. Copy the timestamp of HTTP Request while seeing the log "stop ns transit time: " (HTTP_RES_HDR_SENT)
9. Response_Transit_Time should be HTTP_RES_HDR_SENT - HTTP_RES_HDR
10. X-NS-TRANSIT-TIME should be Request_Transit_Time + Response_Transit_Time

updated_cases.title: Using GRE and Client as ACM to Measure Transmit Time at the Same Time
updated_cases.custom_summary: Using GRE and Client as ACM to Measure Transmit Time at the Same Time
updated_cases.custom_steps:
1. Start a watson log level synthetic to 5 at NSproxy
2. Setup GRE tunneling from GRE agent to Proxy
3. Send a imitaion SSL Client Hello packet from GRE Client and NSClient to www.box.com at the same time
4. Copy the timestamp of HTTP Request while seeing the log "start req transit time: " (HTTP_REQ_HDR_RESUME)
5. Copy the timestamp of HTTP Request while seeing the log "stop req transit time: " (HTTP_REQ_HDR_SENT)
6. Request_Transit_Time should be HTTP_REQ_HDR_SENT - HTTP_REQ_HDR_RESUME
7. Copy the timestamp of HTTP Request while seeing the log "start resp transit time: " (HTTP_RES_HDR)
8. Copy the timestamp of HTTP Request while seeing the log "stop ns transit time: " (HTTP_RES_HDR_SENT)
9. Response_Transit_Time should be HTTP_RES_HDR_SENT - HTTP_RES_HDR
10. X-NS-TRANSIT-TIME should be Request_Transit_Time + Response_Transit_Time
updated_cases.custom_expected:
We should get 2 different value from HTTP Header. One is not having SyntheticProbe id
X-NS-TRANSIT-TIME should be Request_Transit_Time + Response_Transit_Time

updated_cases.title: Synthetic Probe ID
updated_cases.custom_steps:
1. Start a watson log level tcp to 1 at NSproxy
2. Client should not assign a "Synthetic Probe ID"
3. Send a imitaion TCP SYN packet from Client to www.box.com
4. There should be "Got inline conn info ... SyntheticProbe id={id}". And id should be 0
updated_cases.custom_expected: There should be "Got inline conn info ... SyntheticProbe id={id}". And id shouldn't be 0

updated_cases.title: Error Log of Destination Unavailable
updated_cases.custom_steps:
1. Send a imitaion HTTP Request packet from Client to https://alice-offline.webtest.cern.ch/
2. HTTP request should be blocked
3. X-NS-PROXY-STATUS should be set to "destination_unavailable" and sent back to client
4. Client should recived a HTTP packet with X-NS-PROXY-STATUS = destination_unavailable
updated_cases.custom_expected: Client should recived a HTTP packet with X-NS-PROXY-STATUS = destination_unavailable
